Install Oracle VirtualBox on top of Ubuntu OS and set up a Virtual Machine of Windows 10 flavor.

Algorithm:

1.Start.

2.First, make sure that Windows Ubuntu is up-to-date:
  -sudo apt update
  -sudo apt upgrade

3.Install the required dependencies:
  -sudo apt install -y wget software-properties-common

4.Add Oracle VirtualBox Open Keys:
  -wget -q https://www.virtualbox.org/download/oracle_vbox_2016.asc -O- | sudo apt-key add -

5.Add Oracle VirtualBox repository:
  -sudo add-apt-repository "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/debian $$(lsb_release -sc) contrib"

6.Install Virtual Box:
  -sudo apt install virtualbox-7.0 (Based on the handwritten note: sudo apt install virtualbox-7.0)

7.Download Windows 10 ISO from Microsoft official website.

8.Create Virtual Machine for Windows 10:
  -Open Virtual Box.
  -Click 'New' to create a new Virtual Machine.
  -Allocate resources (CPU, RAM, storage).
  -Choose the Windows 10 ISO.
  -Check start and begin Windows 10 installation.
